This paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for diabetic retinopathy grading, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the importance of reference standards and the use of adjudication, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of data and the measurement of performance metrics, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
